"Copyright and Designs Law provides a complete guide to the modern law relating to copyright, including how it relates to the arts, the media (including cable and satellite broadcasting) and the special requirements of new technology. Throughout the work the authors examine and assess the provisions of the Copyright, Designs and Patents Act 1988, guiding the practitioner through the potential minefield of copyright and designs law. The work also takes account of the growing impact of EC law in this dynamic and fast-moving field. This looseleaf work, which is updated twice a year, keeps the practitioner abreast of case law and will prove invaluable to any practitioner working in this field in the wake of the 1988 Act"
